<typeStatus id="54AA886A802ABC5EDE65FEA608B3FEEB" box="[312,415,290,315]" pageId="8" pageNumber="593">lectotype</typeStatus>
(♂): A single examined male labeled “ 
<collectingCountry id="F3067658802ABC5EDC02FEA60AE2FEEB" box="[863,974,290,315]" name="Honduras" pageId="8" pageNumber="593">Honduras</collectingCountry>
/ 
<collectingCountry id="F3067658802ABC5EDCB5FEA70D77FEEB" box="[1000,1115,290,315]" name="Saint Pierre and Miquelon" pageId="8" pageNumber="593">San Pedro</collectingCountry>
Sula / ex. coll. Fruhstorfer” [printed], “ 
<number id="3DD924EF802ABC5EDE4EFEC3081FFE8F" box="[275,307,327,351]" pageId="8" pageNumber="593" value="31.0">31</number>
.”, “ 
<emphasis id="B965EADA802ABC5EDE01FEC30843FE8E" box="[348,367,327,350]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="593">C</emphasis>
. ♂ / 
<taxonomicName id="4C114D4B802ABC5EDEFAFEC208C9FE8E" box="[423,485,326,350]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vidua">
<emphasis id="B965EADA802ABC5EDEFAFEC208C9FE8E" box="[423,485,326,350]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="593">vidua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
/ det. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF804B39802ABC5EDD77FEC20B81FE8F" author="Friese" box="[554,685,326,351]" pageId="8" pageNumber="593" refString="Friese, H. (1898) Die Trigona - Arten Australiens. Termeszetrajzi Fuzetek, 21, 427 - 431." type="journal article" year="1898">
Friese 
<number id="3DD924EF802ABC5EDD28FEC30B81FE8F" box="[629,685,327,351]" pageId="8" pageNumber="593" value="1898.0">1898</number>
</bibRefCitation>
[printed] / Mocs.”, “ 
<typeStatus id="54AA886A802ABC5EDCCEFEC30D06FE8F" box="[915,1066,327,351]" pageId="8" pageNumber="593">HOLOTYPE</typeStatus>
/ 
<taxonomicName id="4C114D4B802ABC5EDB62FEC20DF8FE8F" box="[1087,1236,326,351]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vidua">Centris vidua</taxonomicName>
/ 
<bibRefCitation id="EF804B39802ABC5EDBB7FEC30CBDFE8F" author="Mocsary" box="[1258,1425,327,351]" pageId="8" pageNumber="593" refString="Mocsary, A. (1899) Species novae generis Centris Fabr. in collectione Musaei Nationalis Hungarici. Termeszetrajzi Fuzetek, 22, 251 - 255." type="journal article" year="1899">
Mocsáry, 
<number id="3DD924EF802ABC5EDA0AFEC30CBDFE8F" box="[1367,1425,327,351]" pageId="8" pageNumber="593" value="1899.0">1899</number>
</bibRefCitation>
” [red printed]. Friese must have received this specimen directly from the collection of Hans Fruhstorfer (
<date id="FFAF1008802ABC5EDFC2FE0A080EFE77" box="[159,290,398,423]" pageId="8" pageNumber="593" value="1866" valueMax="1922">
<number id="3DD924EF802ABC5EDFC2FE0A080EFE77" box="[159,290,398,423]" pageId="8" pageNumber="593" value="1894.0" valueMax="1922.0" valueMin="1866.0">1866–1922</number>
</date>
), a naturalist and insect dealer. The 
<typeStatus id="54AA886A802ABC5EDDBBFE0B0A3AFE77" box="[742,790,399,423]" pageId="8" pageNumber="593">type</typeStatus>
locality is 
<collectingCountry id="F3067658802ABC5EDCF5FE0B0D0DFE77" box="[936,1057,398,423]" name="Saint Pierre and Miquelon" pageId="8" pageNumber="593">San Pedro</collectingCountry>
Sula, Cortés, 
<collectingCountry id="F3067658802ABC5EDB8BFE0A0C6AFE77" box="[1238,1350,398,423]" name="Honduras" pageId="8" pageNumber="593">Honduras</collectingCountry>
, where Fruhstorfer apparently never collected (
<bibRefCitation id="EF804B39802ABC5EDD0AFE370BC5FE1B" author="Lamas" box="[599,745,434,459]" pageId="8" pageNumber="593" refString="Lamas, G. (2005) A bibliography of the zoological publications of Hans Fruhstorfer (1866 - 1922). Entomofauna, 26, 57 - 100." type="journal article" year="2005">
Lamas 
<number id="3DD924EF802ABC5EDDF1FE360BC5FE1B" box="[684,745,434,459]" pageId="8" pageNumber="593" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The species was correctly interpreted by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF804B39802ABC5EDB8DFE3609F4FE3F" pageId="8" pageNumber="593" refString="Snelling, R. R. (1984) Studies on the taxonomy and distribution of American Centridine bees (Hymenoptera: Anthophoridae). Contributions in Science Natural History Museum of Los Angeles County, 347, 1 - 69." type="journal article">
Snelling (Snelling 
<number id="3DD924EF802ABC5EDFCAFE5309FCFE3F" box="[151,208,471,495]" pageId="8" pageNumber="593" value="1984.0">1984</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EF804B39802ABC5EDE53FE5308C1FE3F" box="[270,493,470,495]" pageId="8" pageNumber="593" refString="Moure, J. S., Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. (2007) Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell, 1901. In: Moure, J. S., Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Eds.), Catalogue of bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical region, Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba (Parana), pp. 83 - 142." type="book chapter">
Moure 
<emphasis id="B965EADA802ABC5EDE3DFE5308BCFE3E" box="[352,400,470,494]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="593">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number id="3DD924EF802ABC5EDEFAFE5308C9FE3F" box="[423,485,471,495]" pageId="8" pageNumber="593" value="2007.0">2007</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
